external_knowledge:
- The interaction_weighted_score formula takes into account the customer's success rate in interactions (cis.success_rate), interaction rank (cis.interaction_rank), natural logarithm of the account balance (cfd.log_account_balance), and total credit score (ce.total_credit_score / 100); 
- The natural logarithm of the account balance is used to reduce the effect of extreme values; 
- The interaction rank is based on the percentile rank of the interaction count for each customer.

sql:
SELECT customer_id, account_balance
FROM customer_financial_info
WHERE account_balance > '1000.0';

external_knowledge:
- The 'highest education level' refers to the most advanced category achieved by a customer (e.g., graduate degree, undergraduate degree, high school diploma); 
- The 'average account balance' is calculated after removing the currency symbol; 
- 'Engaged multiple times' means the customer has more than one interaction recorded.

- 'owned' home refers to customers who have a home ownership status of 'Owned'; 
- "medium-range credit score" refers to customers with a credit score range of 'Medium', which typically indicates a moderate creditworthiness; 
- 'email' and 'online chat' are preferred marketing channels used by customers to receive marketing communications.
